tags: cant we all just get along
body:
Danaerys, the True Queen

So what I love about GRRM’s world is that strong women rule. Dorne has been ruled by women, Oberon’s mother ruled, his niece (in the books) is next to rule over her brother as the elder. The Dance of Dragons was started over an argument about an elder sister having a better claim over a male descendants. And I get it. Our world and the majority of Planetos is based on a patriarchal society. Taking theories of “Mad Queens” out of the equation, it stings that strong female leadership is so quickly put down because there’s a male heir who is the grandchild of the last Targaryen monarch while Dany is his only living child. I hope they learn from the Dance. Jon and Dany have so many parallels that entwine them together, both have qualities of Azor Ahai and fit into parts of the prophecy, they’re both born of the line of Aerys II, births possibly coincide of the beginnings of White Walker activity…. They’re already in love, just solve your problems and join forces.
